  "body": "I recently tried bumping from Hardhat v2.0.8 to v2.0.9 and noticed all my tests started failing with:\r\n```\r\n     Uncaught Error: Callback was already called.\r\n```\r\n\r\nAt first I thought it might have been some issue with my project setup, but it seems to also affect the template project:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ mkdir hardhat-test; cd hardhat-test\r\n$ yarn init -y\r\n$ yarn add -D hardhat\r\n$ npx hardhat init # Create sample project\r\n...\r\n$ npx hardhat test\r\n...\r\n     Uncaught Error: Callback was already called.\r\n      at /home/foobar/Developer/hardhat-test/node_modules/merkle-patricia-tree/node_modules/async/lib/async.js:43:36\r\n      at WriteStream.<anonymous> (node_modules/merkle-patricia-tree/node_modules/async/lib/async.js:358:17)\r\n      at WriteStream.destroy (node_modules/level-ws/level-ws.js:140:8)\r\n      at finish (_stream_writable.js:670:14)\r\n      at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:80:21)\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nSome environment information (feel free to ask if I missed something important):\r\n```\r\n$ npx hardhat --version\r\n2.0.9\r\n$ node --version\r\nv14.15.1\r\n$ yarn --version\r\n1.22.10\r\n$ cat /etc/redhat-release \r\nFedora release 33 (Thirty Three)\r\n```",
